title: Ensign - Commander
description: Progressed in grade from Ensign to Commander; serving almost seven years on active duty (`73 - `80). While on active duty, I qualified as a Surface Warfare Officer. On sea duty, I served as a Communications Officer, Navigator, and Electronic Material Officer on a Destroyer and on a Destroyer Squadron Staff. Collateral assignments during this period included service as ship’s Intelligence Officer and the Electronic Warfare Officer. On shore duty, I served as an instructor in Mine Warfare, while earning a Master’s Degree in the evenings. After leaving active service, I continued as a drilling reservist until retirement eligible in 1993. Reserve assignments (`80 - `93) included: • Staff Duty Officer/Senior Watch Officer and reserve Operations and Plans Officer for the Military Sealift Command. • Qualified for command, and served as Commanding Officer of three naval reserve units: NR Beachmaster Unit Two, NR FF-1038, and NR FF-1084. • Served as Training Officer and Executive Officer of NR FF-1084.
name: Ted Titcomb
